<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n11056i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11056i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11056i"> 56(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> zero hour </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Zero hour:&nbsp;(a) Mil., the hour at which an attack or operation is timed to begin; also transf.;&nbsp;(b) the hour when something is at its lowest ebb (nonce-use);&nbsp;(c) the hour from which the time of day is measured. <font color="green">[1st instance: 1917 W. BEACH THOMAS <cite>With British on Somme</cite> II. v, The coming of the zero hour of 3.30 in the morning]</font> (<i>OED</i>). See also <a name="n24025f" href="n24all.htm#n24025f">N24 (VI.D.5):025(f)</a>, <a name="n22024b" href="n22all.htm#n22024b">N22 (VI.B.17):024(b)</a>, <a name="n26015h" href="n26all.htm#n26015h">N26 (VI.B.18):015(h)</a> and <a name="n41026b" href="n41all.htm#n41026b">N41 (VI.B.33):026(b)</a>.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c04067f" href="c04all.htm#c04067f">VI.C.04:067(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
